### Log Tool Calls with PreToolUse Hook (Python & TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/nothflare/claude-agent-sdk-docs/blob/main/docs/en/agent-sdk/guides/hooks.md

This snippet demonstrates how to create a hook callback that logs the tool name and input when a 'PreToolUse' event occurs. It accesses 'tool_name' and 'tool_input' from the input data. The Python version uses standard print statements, while the TypeScript version uses console.log and type casting for 'PreToolUseHookInput'.

```python
async def log_tool_calls(input_data, tool_use_id, context):
    if input_data['hook_event_name'] == 'PreToolUse':
        print(f"Tool: {input_data['tool_name']}")
        print(f"Input: {input_data['tool_input']}")
    return {}
```

```typescript
const logToolCalls: HookCallback = async (input, toolUseID, { signal }) => {
  if (input.hook_event_name === 'PreToolUse') {
    const preInput = input as PreToolUseHookInput;
    console.log(`Tool: ${preInput.tool_name}`);
    console.log(`Input:`, preInput.tool_input);
  }
  return {};
};
```

